## Error Handling

### If Git Status Check Fails
Stop immediately and report:
- Current branch
- Uncommitted changes (if any)
- Distance from origin/main
- Recommendation: User should resolve manually

### If File Content Conflicts
- Report which files have inconsistent information
- Suggest alignment approach
- Do not auto-resolve without clarification

### If Update Seems Incomplete
- List what's missing
- Ask for clarification on content
- Do not force completion

---

## Communication

### Report After Each Update
Include:
- Files modified
- Lines added/changed
- Git commit hash
- Status: "Successfully pushed to origin/main" or error details

### When Asking for Clarification
Be specific:
- What information is unclear
- What options exist
- Which file/section is affected
- What decision is needed

